The get_request_handler function in fastapi/routing.py creates an async request handler that processes incoming requests. Lines 177-184 show the body parsing logic:

```python
async def app(request: Request) -> Response:
    try:
        body = None
        if body_field:
            if is_body_form:
                body = await request.form()
            else:
                body_bytes = await request.body()
                if body_bytes:
                    body = await request.json()  # Line 184 - NO Content-Type check
```

The critical issue is that `request.json()` is called without any prior validation of the Content-Type header. This means requests with Content-Type: text/plain or other non-JSON types will still be parsed as JSON if they contain valid JSON data.
